main event: On August 22, 1956, three round objects were observed for thirty-five minutes, characterized by a red and green light revolving around a white light.
interesting points: The objects were the size of a pea at arm's length, and the observation was made both visually and through binoculars.
Possible conclusions included the objects being ball shaped, aircraft, a balloon, or an astronomical phenomenon, with insufficient data for evaluation.
In another sighting report on the same date, witnesses observed a bright white object emitting brilliant light at high altitude, moving in air speed pattern near Wright Patterson Dayton Ohio.
The report lacks photographs or images despite the detailed sightings and observations provided.
The document demonstrates the efforts of Project Blue Book in collecting and analyzing data on UFO sightings, including the use of optical character recognition to process reports.
sighted object: three round objects with red and green lights
location: Marshalltown, Iowa, and Wright Patterson Dayton Ohio
witnesses: Colette Estill and her son, as well as other unidentified witnesses
